Input
\layout Standard
\added_space_bottom bigskip 
The code is run without parameters in the command line:
\layout Standard
\added_space_bottom bigskip 

\family typewriter 
vafm 
\layout Standard
\noindent 
The code reads in a single input file 
\family typewriter 
virtual.inp,
\family default 
and will produce a number of output files; the main one is called 
\family typewriter 
virtual.out
\family default 
, but some others are also produced
\emph on 
 
\emph default 
depending on
\emph on 
 
\emph default 
the calculation type (see section 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{sec:Output}

\end_inset 

).
\layout Standard
\added_space_bottom smallskip \noindent \align left 
The input file is separated into specific boxes for each category of input
 parameters.
 Each box begins with the 
\emph on 
keyword
\emph default 
 name of the box in the format
\family typewriter 
 
\layout Standard
\added_space_bottom smallskip \align left 

\family typewriter 
.<keyword>
\emph on 
 
\layout Standard
\align left 
and then the appropriate keywords and parameters for that box are listed
 until the box end marker
\layout Standard
\added_space_top smallskip \added_space_bottom smallskip \align left 

\family typewriter 
.<End>
\layout Standard
\align left 
is found.
 Keywords must be placed in the input box they are classed in, they will
 be ignored in other boxes.
 All the keywords require another controlling word or parameter value.
 After the example file, each box and its keywords are explained, along
 with possible parameters which can be used.
 All quantities are inputed in the SI units.
\layout Standard

Comments can be entered into the input file by placing ## before the line.
 Empty lines will be ignored.
 There is no specific order required for the boxes in the input file and
 for the keywords within each box; however, in some rare cases there is
 some order needed for specific keywords within the boxes.
 These position dependent keywords will be highlighted below.
\layout Subsection

Example Input File
\begin_inset LatexCommand \label{sub:Example-Input-File}

\end_inset 


\layout Standard

This input file below runs altogether 29 stages of the virtual machine.
 The first two stages are needed to stabilise the cantilever, they are not
 shown in the box 
\family typewriter 
\size footnotesize 
.<Elementary_Stages>
\family default 
\size default 
 since are run anyway (default).
 The 3rd stage corresponds to the approach of the tip to the surface to
 get the -440 Hz frequency shift.
 After this stage the tip scans along the 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset 

 direction for 0.02 s.
 Then a 2D scan starts which consists of 3 sequencies of 4 elementary line
 scans (passages) each, 12 elementary line scans altogether.
 The scan is performed keeping the same frequency shift and amplitude.
 This first 2D scan is followed by a single stage in which the tip is not
 moved laterally, but the amplitude is reduced by 10 
\begin_inset ERT
status Collapsed

\layout Standard

\backslash 
AA 
\end_inset 

.
 Finally, the second scan is performed, identical to the first one with
 the original amplitude and frequency shift.
